The paper deals with the complexity of Promise Constraint Satisfaction Problems (PCSPs), which are a generalization of Constraint Satisfaction Problems (CSPs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), which deals with the study of the inherent difficulty of computational problems. The paper also discusses the reduction of PCSPs to CSPs, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses concepts from logic (cs.LO) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) to prove its main result.
